-- File: supabase/migrations/00162_meramec_niangua_geometry_extend.sql
-- Extend two curated mainstems whose lines stopped short of their own
-- rating gauges, leaving those gauges rendering as "phantom" markers in a
-- blank basin on /river-map:
--
--   * meramec: the line began ~10 river-miles DOWNSTREAM of USGS 07010350
--     (Meramec River at Cook Station) — the whole upper Meramec was missing.
--     Prepends the mainstem from the headwaters near Salem through Cook
--     Station down to the old upstream end.
--   * niangua: the line ended ~4 miles UPSTREAM of USGS 06923950 (Niangua
--     River at Tunnel Dam) — appends the mainstem down through the gauge.
--
-- Source: USGS NLDI mainstem navigation (UM/DM flowlines from the NWIS
-- sites, NHDPlus HR geometry). The shared origin reach that appears in both
-- navigations is proximity-trimmed (no double-traversal), lines are
-- Douglas-Peucker simplified at ~25 m, and quality-gated: zero
-- self-overlaps, junction gaps ≤ 235 ft, no segment over 0.8 mi (the
-- pre-existing line ships 2 mi segments). Verified post-extend: 07010350
-- sits 0.02 mi from the meramec line and 06923950 sits 0.02 mi from the
-- niangua line; every other mainstem gauge is unchanged at 0.00 mi.
-- (07018500 Big River at Byrnesville and 07017200 Big River at Irondale
-- remain intentionally off-line — proxy raters on a stream the map does
-- not draw; the map hides off-line gauge markers.)
--
-- ST_NPoints guards make re-application a no-op (the extension must not be
-- prepended twice): meramec is 551 points before / ~916 after, niangua 330
-- before / ~394 after.

